## 2️⃣ Configure Git (Global & Local Config)

### 🔹 Global Configuration

Global config applies to all repositories in the system.

```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your-email@example.com"
git config --global --list
```

### Screenshot:

📸 *Attach screenshot of global git config list*

---

### 🔹 Local Configuration

Local config applies only to a specific repository.

```bash
git config user.name "Local Name"
git config user.email "local-email@example.com"
git config --list
```

